	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>107 Mac Dougal St</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>3d June&#47;59</date></p>
				<p>Rev Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The committee of ar<lb/>rangements at <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> have<lb/> invited me to consecrate their<lb/> Synagogue &#38; I have accepted<lb/> the invitation.  This morning I<lb/> receive a letter from them dated<lb/> <date>31<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date> Ulto. In which they say to me<lb/> that they <sic>inclose</sic> &#8220;the &#39;order<lb/> of service&#39; not having any<lb/> one here capable of translating<lb/> them&#44; would solicit you to<lb/> translate and have them printed<lb/> on one side Hebrew and on the<lb/> other side English&#8212;there being<lb/> a number of German members<lb/> of our congregation it is likewise<lb/> desired that some be printed<lb/> in the Hebrew and German languages.<lb/>  The whole number to be printed<lb/> is 600 copies say 500 Heb &#38; Engl.<lb/> and 100 Heb. &#38; Germ.  It is also</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>suggested that the printing be<lb/> awarded to the <persName>Rev Isaac Leeser</persName><lb/> &#38; that when done they be forwarded<lb/> here by express with <persName>Billy</persName> for paymt.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In compliance with their<lb/> suggestion&#44; you will oblige me<lb/> by letting me know whether you<lb/> will undertake the printing<lb/> &#38; engage to have the 600 copies<lb/> delivered at <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> on or before<lb/> <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June</date>.  It will make about<lb/> 14 pages&#44; including the Title.  I<lb/> should also like to know if you<lb/> prefer the German translation<lb/> in this sort of writing or in<lb/> German text.  The folks at<lb/> <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> do not say how they<lb/> wish their German printed so<lb/> you must exercise your own<lb/> discretion&#44; &#38; use that sort of<lb/> type which you have most<lb/> readily at hand.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As I fear your reply</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>by post will not reach me<lb/> till <date>Tuesday</date> morning&#44; and I should<lb/> like to send you the manuscript<lb/> by <date>Monday</date> afternoon mail<lb/> please reply to my questions<lb/> by Telegraph&#44; as soon after<lb/> receipt of this as <add>Hebrew</add> will<lb/> permit</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Wishing you <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> I am Rev Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours very respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">M J Raphall Dr.</persName></p>
		</body>
